<span id="freeTextContainer12385744453377143416">One of Heinrich Boell&apos;s better-known works is this 1963 novel about an embittered, satirical clown who despises postwar Germany for its hypocrisy and empty materialism. Insightful and well worth reading either in this translation or in the original title, <i>Ansichten eines Clowns</i>.</span>
  <span id="freeText12385744453377143416" style="display:none">One of Heinrich Boell's better-known works is this 1963 novel about an embittered, satirical clown who despises postwar Germany for its hypocrisy and empty materialism. Insightful and well worth reading either in this translation or in the original title, <i>Ansichten eines Clowns</i>.</span>
